# LinkedIn Post Generator — Complete System Deep Dive

## What Is This Tool? (The Big Picture)

This is a **LinkedIn content marketing automation system** built for **Obsidian Logic AI**. It takes a topic (or existing content from LinkedIn/YouTube) and generates a ready-to-publish LinkedIn post — complete with caption text and visual assets (images, carousels, video concepts). Think of it as a **content repurposing factory** that can:

1. **Research** what's going viral on LinkedIn and YouTube
2. **Analyze** competitor content strategies
3. **Generate** original LinkedIn posts using AI (Gemini 3.0)
4. **Create visuals** (images, carousels) to accompany the posts
5. **Track costs** per generation run
6. **Save** approved content to a database (Baserow)

---

## The Architecture (How Everything Connects)

The tool follows a **3-layer architecture** — the same pattern described in [GEMINI.md](file:///c:/LinkedIn%20Post%20Generator%20v1.1/GEMINI.md):

```mermaid
graph TD
    A["🖥️ Frontend SPA<br/>(index.html + script.js + style.css)"] -->|HTTP POST / SSE Stream| B["⚙️ Backend Server<br/>(server.py — FastAPI on :9999)"]
    B -->|Subprocess Call| C["🔧 Orchestrator<br/>(orchestrator.py)"]
    C -->|Routes to| D["📝 generate_assets.py<br/>(Single Posts)"]
    C -->|Routes to| E["📊 generate_carousel.py<br/>(Carousel Posts)"]
    D -->|Reads| F["📋 Directives<br/>(directives/*.md)"]
    E -->|Reads| F
    D -->|Calls| G["🤖 Gemini 3.0 API<br/>(Text + Image Gen)"]
    E -->|Calls| G
    B -->|Research Endpoints| H["🔍 Apify Scrapers<br/>(viral_research_apify.py)"]
    B -->|YouTube| I["📹 yt-dlp<br/>(local_youtube.py)"]
    B -->|Save| J["💾 Baserow DB<br/>(baserow_logger.py)"]
```

| Layer | What It Does | Key Files |
|-------|-------------|-----------|
| **Layer 1: Directives** | SOPs (Standard Operating Procedures) written in Markdown that tell the AI *how* to write each type of post | `directives/*.md` |
| **Layer 2: Orchestration** | Decision-making — reads the user request, routes it to the right generator, manages temp files | [orchestrator.py](file:///c:/LinkedIn%20Post%20Generator%20v1.1/orchestrator.py), [server.py](file:///c:/LinkedIn%20Post%20Generator%20v1.1/server.py) |
| **Layer 3: Execution** | Deterministic Python scripts that do the actual work: API calls, scraping, image generation | `execution/*.py` |

