## Complete Workflow (Step by Step)

### Flow 1: Fresh Post Generation

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User (Browser)
    participant F as Frontend (script.js)
    participant S as Server (server.py)
    participant O as Orchestrator
    participant G as generate_assets.py
    participant AI as Gemini 3.0 API

    U->>F: Fill form (topic, type, purpose, visual)
    F->>S: POST /api/generate-stream (SSE)
    S->>O: subprocess.Popen(orchestrator.py ...)
    O->>O: Clear .tmp/ (PRE-CLEAR/POST-CLEAR)
    O->>G: subprocess(generate_assets.py ...)
    G->>G: Load directive (e.g. educational_caption.md)
    G-->>S: >>>STAGE:text_start (stdout)
    G->>AI: Send mega prompt + directive + visual context
    AI-->>G: JSON response (caption, image_prompt, etc.)
    G-->>S: >>>STAGE:text_done (stdout)
    G-->>S: >>>STAGE:image_start (stdout)
    G->>AI: Generate image from prompt
    AI-->>G: Image bytes
    G-->>S: >>>STAGE:image_done (stdout)
    G->>G: Save final_plan.json to .tmp/
    S-->>F: SSE events (stage updates + final result)
    F->>U: Display caption + image in Output Console
```

### Flow 2: Repurposing Existing Content

This is the **killer feature**. The user finds viral/competitor content and remixes it:

1. **Research phase**: User searches for viral posts, competitor profiles, or YouTube videos
2. **Select & Repurpose**: User clicks "Repurpose" on any result
3. **Modal opens**: Shows source content preview, visual context indicator (how many images/videos were found), and the full 128-option routing form
4. **Generate**: Same pipeline as fresh generation, but with rich source context (original text, images, video transcripts) injected into the AI prompt

### Flow 3: Research Only (No Generation)

The Competitor Hub has three research modes:

| Tab | What It Does | Script Used | External Service |
|-----|-------------|-------------|-----------------|
| **Viral** | Search LinkedIn for viral posts on a topic | [viral_research_apify.py](file:///c:/LinkedIn%20Post%20Generator%20v1.1/execution/viral_research_apify.py) | Apify LinkedIn Scraper |
| **Competitor** | Scrape a specific LinkedIn profile's recent posts | [research_competitors.py](file:///c:/LinkedIn%20Post%20Generator%20v1.1/execution/research_competitors.py) + [viral_research_apify.py](file:///c:/LinkedIn%20Post%20Generator%20v1.1/execution/viral_research_apify.py) | Apify LinkedIn Scraper |
| **YouTube** | Extract video metadata + transcripts from YouTube URLs | [local_youtube.py](file:///c:/LinkedIn%20Post%20Generator%20v1.1/execution/local_youtube.py) (fast) or [apify_youtube.py](file:///c:/LinkedIn%20Post%20Generator%20v1.1/execution/apify_youtube.py) (deep) | yt-dlp (free) or Apify |

