## Why Do All These Files/Skills Exist?

### "Why so many directives?"
Each directive is a different **content playbook framework**. The client's marketing strategy uses 4 frameworks (Breakdown, Announcement, Money Math, ID-Challenge), and each has both a caption (short) and article (long) variant. Plus supporting directives for visuals, research, and brand knowledge. **This is the core IP of the tool.**

### "Why so many execution scripts?"
Each script handles one specific job: one for generating posts, one for generating carousels, one for research, one for YouTube, one for tracking costs, etc. This follows the **3-layer architecture principle** — push complexity into deterministic scripts so errors don't compound.

### "Why the `.agent/skills/` folder with 252 files?"
These are **instructions for the AI coding agent** (tools like me). They tell the AI how to write code for this project (brand colors, design system, how to handle errors, etc.). They are NOT runtime dependencies of the LinkedIn tool. You can strip them out when integrating.

### "Why `history.json` and `TROUBLESHOOTING.md`?"
- `history.json` = local log of every generation run (412KB of client data — **exclude this**)
- `TROUBLESHOOTING.md` = documented bugs and their fixes. This is a **learning document** from the self-annealing loop described in `GEMINI.md`

